description._content: Description: Group of over mature Troodos Pine - Pinus nigra var. Karamanica, Elevation 5,700 feet, with younger age classes, practically a Cyprus form of selection forest. Troodos Forest, Elevation 5,700 feet. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: View North East of the Military Camp under snow, Troodos Forest, middle elevation 5,600 feet. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives.
